reviews.review: There is absolutely nothing to compare to this movie, I loved every second of it, the only thing I wish was that it won't be the end of any of the characters stories, Rey, Finn, or Poe, I would love to see a spin-off movie or Disney Plus series of a number of things that we saw in just this movie alone.  Now it absolutely could've been better, but with the unfortunate passing of Carrie Fisher, they did the best that they could do, and I was honestly worried because of her passing, and I'm nothing short of impressed with how they filled it.

The 3rd component of Kathleen Kennedy's Frankenstein's monster of a trilogy goes out on a very sour note. JJ and Chris Terrio failed in nearly every aspect in this movie's screenplay, a movie that is basically a large exposition dump that makes not a lick of sense. It pained me to watch this. I wanted to like it very much, i hoped the critics were wrong. But the entire film i found myself facepalming over how ridiculous, corny, and dissapointing it was from beginning to end. Ian McDiarmid is the standout (as expected) and once again shines in a turd of a movie. The actors did their jobs well all around, and there were some really good looking scenes and setpieces here and there, but ultimately fail to hold up the baffling story and direction. Sorry what they did to your ideas George Lucas.
Thank you for fixing the last movie!

Phenomenal. As a kid of the 70’s & 80’s I grew up with Star Wars...and boy did Star Wars: TROS deliver. I’m not sure what “critics” or anyone below 4 stars wants from a movie. Our HS age daughters loved it too. Can’t wait to see it again.
Such a great movie! Saw it 3 times and loved it! Fixes everything Last Jedi messed up and ends the trilogy perfectly. My favorite Star Wars movie from the Skywalker trilogy!

I didn't like that certain characters died.
several thematic inconsistencies

It was exciting and emotional and a very good end to the saga. There are always going to be the people who decide the new Star Wars movie is bad before it even comes out. For everyone else, it was an awesome movie!
